./docs/sprint-memos/7h-42-V7d-split-review.codex.log:4714:5120:399:   399	- 2026-04-26 [conventions-doc][reduces-task-body-overhead] **A single canonical CONVENTIONS doc inside the artifact directory it governs (here: `keeper_sdk/core/schemas/CONVENTIONS.md`) removes ~30% of per-task redundant context.** Before: every P*-impl task body re-derived `additionalProperties: false`, `x-keeper-live-proof` block shape, `$id` pattern, cross-family ref grammar, `uid_ref` semantic uniqueness pattern, `$comment` TODO marker convention, commit-message format. After: task body cites CONVENTIONS by path; worker reads it first; task body shrinks to the family-specific scope only. Workers propose amendments via DONE-dump LESSON CANDIDATE; parent integrates after 2+ families hit the same pattern (don't amend on a single-family quirk). Pattern: when 3+ artifact instances share 80%+ of their construction rules, factor the rules into a CONVENTIONS doc colocated with the artifacts. The doc becomes parent-owned; workers cite, don't edit.
./docs/sprint-memos/7h-42-V7d-split-review.codex.log:4716:5122:416:   416	- 2026-04-27 [capability-census][three-gates] **Treat schema status, provider slice, and live-proof transcript as three SEPARATE gates; only families with all three should claim "supported".** Sprint 7h-36 CDX-3 surfaced the canonical mismatch: `pam-environment.v1` had 2/3 gates green (provider apply works, transcript via smoke matrix), but missed the schema metadata gate (`x-keeper-live-proof` block absent at `pam-environment.v1.schema.json:1-8` while `CONVENTIONS.md:27-40` required it for every family). Mechanical fix landed `bffa01b`. Vault L1 has 0/3 — code wired (`vault_models.py`, `vault_graph.py`, `vault_diff.py`, `commander_cli.py:786`) but schema still `scaffold-only`, no smoke scenario, no transcript. Pattern: every status-bump PR description must explicitly check all 3 gates with cited evidence; partial bumps accumulate doc-vs-code drift that costs downstream worker cycles.
./docs/sprint-memos/7h-42-V7d-split-review.codex.log:4718:5126:445:   445	- 2026-04-27 [codex-prompts][sprint-templates-vs-prefabs] **`tasks/PREFAB_*.md` is full bodies for repeated workloads; `templates/SPRINT_*.md` is skeletons with `${VAR}` placeholders for the per-sprint slice patterns the orchestrator hand-writes ~5x per sprint. Three templates land 7h-40 V5c: offline-write-feature, readonly-memo, live-proof.** Each ends with an LESSONS-derived anti-patterns section that the orchestrator updates whenever a new violation surfaces (drift policy: snippet edits go through LESSONS.md first, then the template, with version: bump). Pattern: when a sprint prompt structure repeats >3 times, extract the skeleton to a `templates/SPRINT_*.md` and cite origin sprints in the header.
./docs/sprint-memos/7h-42-V7d-split-review.codex.log:4720:5139:   416	- 2026-04-27 [capability-census][three-gates] **Treat schema status, provider slice, and live-proof transcript as three SEPARATE gates; only families with all three should claim "supported".** Sprint 7h-36 CDX-3 surfaced the canonical mismatch: `pam-environment.v1` had 2/3 gates green (provider apply works, transcript via smoke matrix), but missed the schema metadata gate (`x-keeper-live-proof` block absent at `pam-environment.v1.schema.json:1-8` while `CONVENTIONS.md:27-40` required it for every family). Mechanical fix landed `bffa01b`. Vault L1 has 0/3 — code wired (`vault_models.py`, `vault_graph.py`, `vault_diff.py`, `commander_cli.py:786`) but schema still `scaffold-only`, no smoke scenario, no transcript. Pattern: every status-bump PR description must explicitly check all 3 gates with cited evidence; partial bumps accumulate doc-vs-code drift that costs downstream worker cycles.
