./docs/sprint-memos/7h-40-V5d-operator-bootstrap.codex.log:6226:   416	- 2026-04-27 [capability-census][three-gates] **Treat schema status, provider slice, and live-proof transcript as three SEPARATE gates; only families with all three should claim "supported".** Sprint 7h-36 CDX-3 surfaced the canonical mismatch: `pam-environment.v1` had 2/3 gates green (provider apply works, transcript via smoke matrix), but missed the schema metadata gate (`x-keeper-live-proof` block absent at `pam-environment.v1.schema.json:1-8` while `CONVENTIONS.md:27-40` required it for every family). Mechanical fix landed `bffa01b`. Vault L1 has 0/3 — code wired (`vault_models.py`, `vault_graph.py`, `vault_diff.py`, `commander_cli.py:786`) but schema still `scaffold-only`, no smoke scenario, no transcript. Pattern: every status-bump PR description must explicitly check all 3 gates with cited evidence; partial bumps accumulate doc-vs-code drift that costs downstream worker cycles.
./docs/sprint-memos/7h-40-V5d-operator-bootstrap.codex.log:6239:   429	- 2026-04-27 [orchestration][live-worker-may-bypass-linked-worktree-ref] **A codex live-mode worker can land its commit on `origin/<branch>` without updating the linked-worktree's local branch ref or clearing its working-tree diff.** Symptoms after worker reports DONE: `git ls-remote origin <branch>` shows new SHA, but in the linked worktree `git log` shows the OLD base SHA and `git status` shows the same files as " M" (modified vs HEAD). Cause: live-mode codex appears to commit via plumbing or its own gitdir handling (different from offline-bg's auto-add-dir patch from LESSON `[orchestration][parent-commit]`). Recovery: skip the worktree entirely — parent merges `origin/<branch>` directly from the primary repo with `git merge --no-ff origin/<branch>`, then runs pytest in primary, pushes, and `git worktree remove --force` the dirty linked tree. The dirty diff there is just a stale copy of what's now on main, so `--force` removal is safe. Don't try to reconcile the linked worktree's HEAD — it's a distraction. Future fix in `codex_live.sh`: print local HEAD + remote HEAD after commit so the parent can spot the divergence in the launcher log immediately.
